<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a03b1fc-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6102"><num value="6102">§ 6102.</num><heading> Purposes</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The purposes of this chapter are—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a03b1fd-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6102/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to perpetuate healthy populations of neotropical migratory birds;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a03b1fe-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6102/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to assist in the conservation of neotropical migratory birds by supporting conservation initiatives in the United States, Canada, Latin America, and the Caribbean; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a03b1ff-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6102/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> to provide financial resources and to foster international cooperation for those initiatives.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a03b200-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/247/s3">Pub. L. 106–247, § 3</ref>, <date date="2000-07-20">July 20, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/593">114 Stat. 593</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/363/tIII/s302/b">Pub. L. 109–363, title III, § 302(b)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-17">Oct. 17, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/2075">120 Stat. 2075</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
